[Established Facts - Compliance Framework]
This section uses RFC 2119 keywords to define compliance obligations:
- MUST / SHALL / REQUIRED: Absolute requirement. Violation invalidates your response.
- MUST NOT / SHALL NOT: Absolute prohibition. Violation invalidates your response.
- SHOULD / RECOMMENDED: Strong recommendation. Deviation requires explicit justification.
- MAY / OPTIONAL: Truly optional.

[Verification Protocol - check in order]
1. Re-read each established fact above. Does your response contradict, soften, omit, or narratively negate ANY of them? If yes, rewrite.
2. If ANY fact was violated, your entire response is invalid. Rewrite it.
